dc_description_s: Geological Survey of New Jersey. Atlas Sheet 36 (1907) New Jersey Geological Survey Relief shown by 10 ft. (5 ft. in Cape May Co.) contour intervals and spot heights. Depths shown by 10 ft. contour and soundings in feet at mean or half tide. Inset: eastward continuation of map. Title was not given. Region covered: parts of Atlantic and Cape May counties. Original survey 1883-4. Principal culture revised 1907.The shore lines of tidal waters, and the triangulation are in part from the U.S. Coast and Geodetic Survey. The shore lines of the beaches, the highways, railroads and some other details were revised between 1905 and 1907.
dc_publisher_s: Trenton, N.J. : Geological Survey of New Jersey, 1907.
